    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - CYLINDER SLEEVE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CYLINDER SLEEVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>O-RING INSTALLATION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the O-Rings with clean engine oil and install one into each cylinder sleeve
                    groove, (without twist). Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_119.xml" xrefid="ef4150656">6.56</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Each cylinder sleeve uses three O-Rings.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, assure the proper shim(s) is installed, in the crankcase counterbore, so
                    cylinder sleeve protrusion is within specifications. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150604.xml" xrefid="hl4150604">"CYLINDER SLEEVE FITTING
                        PROCEDURE"</hotlnk>,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_104.xml" xrefid="ef4150604">6.4</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
